properties.abstract: The Gantrisch-Panoramaweg Path offers a scenic pre-Alps hike with many spectacular viewpoints. The tour takes place on a well structured and signposted hiking path – and is a tour suitable for undertaking in stages.
properties.description:
The Gantrisch-Panoramaweg leads over the outskirts of the towns Berne, Fribourg and Thun – and is one of the most beautiful panorama paths in this pre-Alps region. To the south the Gantrisch chain with Nüneneflue, Gantrisch, Bürgle and Ochse seems close enough to touch – and more distant the snow-capped peaks of the Alps are seen. North, views extend over the Schwarzenburgerland and Berne midlands as far as Lake Biel and Jura – and on cloudless days, as far as Feldberg in the Black Forest and the Titlis and Pilatus summits.

From the starting point in Zollhaus/FR by Plaffeien the path leads over Hällstett and the Horbüel-pass to Pfyffe, and further over the Gäggersteg (wooden-stair-climb) to Süftene (hiker’s bus stop). The hiking path then continues over Schüpfeflue to the Selibuel viewpoint. After the Gurnigel Berghaus destination, the path descends northbound to the endpoint Gurnigelbad.  A pleasurable hike with numerous lookouts, seating banks and picnic and rest places along the way!
